  "description": "Canonical registry of research knobs (plan 0018). Every game record dumps the resolved value of these via KnobRegistry.resolve_all, so any two records \u2014 from any sweep \u2014 sit in a common knob-space and are comparable. Adding a knob is a deliberate one-line entry here. Each 'path' is a file prefix + a JsonPath: prefix 'scenario:' resolves against the ACTIVE scenario file (variants work), '<data/rel/file.json>:' is a literal file; the dot-path/array grammar after ':' is JsonPath's (scripts/JsonPath.gd header is the canonical spec \u2014 'name[*]'/'name[]' = every array element, 'name[N]' = one). 'kind' replaces 'path' for values not in a data file (llm_model from env, prompt_hash from the sidecar). 'sweepable': true = overridable via DataOverrides (scalars AND array knobs, e.g. sweep beaches[*].capacity_battalions to scale every beach at once); false = dump-only. DISTINCT from scenario content \u2014 see hexcombat-config-and-knobs.",
